Git repositories almost always have more than one author. Sometimes the original author has the most number of commits, and you can search for the author that way.

One way to do this is by using the [command](https://www.commandlinefu.com/commands/view/4519/list-all-authors-of-a-particular-git-project):

```
git log --format=&#39;%aN &lt;%aE&gt;&#39; | awk &#39;{arr[$0]++} END{for (i in arr){print arr[i], i;}}&#39; | sort -rn | cut -f2- | head -1
```

This command gets the authors, sorts by the number of commits, and then outputs the first result.

You can add it to your Jenkinsfile in a `sh` block.

```groovy
pipeline {
  stages {
    stage(&quot;Checkout&quot;) {
      steps {
        git([url: &#39;xxxxxxxxxx.git&#39;, branch: &quot;master&quot;])
        sh &#39;cd xxxxxxxxx.git&#39;
        sh &#39;git log --format=\&#39;%aN &lt;%aE&gt;\&#39; | awk \&#39;{arr[$0]++} END{for (i in arr){print arr[i], i;}}\&#39; | sort -rn | cut -f2- | head -1 &gt;author.txt&#39;
        sh &#39;cat author.txt&#39;
      }
    }
  }
}

